definition.value: A fenchane monoterpenoid that is bicyclo[2.2.1]heptane substituted by methyl groups at positions 1, 3 and 3 and a hydroxy group at position 2 (the 1S,2S,4R stereoisomer).
A beta-D-Glcp-(1->4)-D-Galp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has beta configuration.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of D-glucopyranose and D-galactopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A  phenethylamine alkaloid that is 2-phenylethanamine substituted by a methyl group at the amino nitrogen and a methyl and a hydroxy group at position 2 and 1 respectively.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of alpha-D-mannopyranose and beta-D-galacopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
